name: Cassiopeia
title: the Serpent's Embrace
shortBio: Cassiopeia is a deadly creature bent on manipulating others to her sinister will. Youngest and most beautiful daughter of the noble Du Couteau family of Noxus, she ventured deep into the crypts beneath Shurima in search of ancient power. There, she was bitten by a gruesome tomb guardian, whose venom transformed her into a viper-like predator. Cunning and agile, Cassiopeia now slithers under the veil of night, petrifying her enemies with her baleful gaze.

skins.name: Desperada Cassiopeia
skins.description: Enterprising creatures of the Old West often fall in with more successful bandit clans, serving as nightmarish enforcers, unafraid of a little casual violence. Cassiopeia became infamous as one such outlaw, but following a bloody coup now leads an enclave of her own.

skins.name: Siren Cassiopeia
skins.description: A humanoid marine serpent known for luring sailors to their deaths, Cassiopeia has a bad reputation and wants to set the record straight. She'd need to stop turning interviewers to stone for that to work, but at least she's trying.

skins.name: Mythic Cassiopeia
skins.description: On a cliff overlooking the sea, the lonely gorgon Cassiopeia has made her home among a garden of statues of her own making. Memories of friends, enemies, and lovers passed, immortalized in stone, many eternally screaming in agony. Whispers from the local villages warn not to enter her domain, but still, visitors keep coming, all to meet the same fate.

skins.name: Jade Fang Cassiopeia
skins.description: An adherent to the teachings of the legendary jade dragon, Cassiopeia keeps its archaic rituals secret and the beast's true nature shrouded in mystery. In recognition she has been granted a fragment of the creature's power, and awaits the day when it will drown the world in evil.

skins.name: Eternum Cassiopeia
skins.description: In a world overrun by alien machines, this one seems especially intrigued by your presence. Its lithe, metal form slides toward you, begging for your attention. You take one look, and—

skins.description: There once was a princess as clever as she was beautiful, who harbored a bitter feud with her sister. Convinced she was the rightful heir to the throne, she tried to poison her rival—but instead, serpent scales bloomed across her soft skin. The Alluring Serpent disappeared that night into the mountains, but the faithful still seek her counsel to this day.

skins.description: They came to Cassiopeia as a shadow within the fog—the shape of the Silver Cobra, slithering up from the numberless graves of the ancient dead. She now stalks the ruling families of humankind, her sculpture garden full of wayward souls who strayed too far from the safety of castle walls, now eternally frozen in the throes of terror.

skins.description: Cassiopeia found herself on the receiving end of a potion gone wrong when a venomous viper slithered into her bubbling cauldron. No longer able to ride her broom, she skulks about the party, hoping to catch the eyes of unsuspecting socialites. With the tail of a snake came… its appetite.

skins.name: Prestige Mythmaker Cassiopeia
skins.description: At the dawn of time, the goddess Cassiopeia prepares to create humanity using the five elements. But when the Paper World is suddenly changed, Cassiopeia creates something unexpected: a cruel artist who embodies what she fears most in herself. Now, she must repair the damage her creation has inflicted upon the land before he destroys it for good.

passive.name: Serpentine Grace
passive.description: Cassiopeia gains Move Speed per level, but she cannot purchase Boots items.

spells.name: Noxious Blast
spells.description: Cassiopeia blasts an area with Poison after a brief delay, granting her increased Move Speed if she hits an enemy champion.
spells.dynamicDescription: Cassiopeia blasts noxious gas, <keywordMajor>Poisoning</keywordMajor> enemies and dealing <magicDamage>@TooltipTotalDamage@ magic damage</magicDamage> over @Effect2Amount@ seconds. Hitting a champion grants Cassiopeia <speed>@Effect3Amount@% Move Speed</speed> decaying over @Effect4Amount@ seconds.@SpellModifierDescriptionAppend@

spells.name: Miasma
spells.description: Cassiopeia releases several clouds of poison, slowing, grounding, and lightly damaging enemies that pass through them. Grounded enemies cannot use Movement abilities.
spells.dynamicDescription: Cassiopeia spews venom, leaving toxic clouds for @Effect4Amount@ seconds. Enemies in the clouds take <magicDamage>@DamagePerSecond@ magic damage</magicDamage> per second, are <keywordMajor>Poisoned</keywordMajor>, <status>Grounded</status>, and <status>Slowed</status> by @Effect2Amount@%.@SpellModifierDescriptionAppend@

spells.name: Twin Fang
spells.description: Cassiopeia lets loose an attack that deals increased damage to Poisoned targets and heals her for a percentage of the damage dealt. If the target dies from this attack, Cassiopeia regains Mana.
spells.dynamicDescription:
Cassiopeia launches deadly fangs, dealing @BasicDamage@ magic damage. If the enemy is Poisoned, they take an additional @BonusPoisonedDamage@ magic damage and Cassiopeia restores @HealCalc@ Health, reduced to @HealCalcMinion@ Health against lane minions and small monsters.

If this kills the target, Cassiopeia restores @Cost@ Mana.

@SpellModifierDescriptionAppend@

spells.name: Petrifying Gaze
spells.description: Cassiopeia releases a swirl of magical energy from her eyes, stunning any enemies in front of her that are facing her and slowing any others with their back turned.
spells.dynamicDescription: Cassiopeia unleashes a petrifying gaze, dealing <magicDamage>@RDamage@ magic damage</magicDamage> and <status>Stunning</status> enemies facing her for @RCCDuration@ seconds. Enemies facing away are <status>Slowed</status> by @RSlowPercent@% decaying over the same duration instead.@SpellModifierDescriptionAppend@
